sub_title: PhD Candidate in Creator Economy & Culture | #SciComm TikTok Creator
summary:
Experienced in research in academic and start-up environments. I am writing a PhD dissertation about platform labour and creator economy. In order to truly understand and appreciate what is happening in society, I am integrating big data with thick data using qualitative, ethnographic research methods that uncover people’s emotions, stories and models of their world. 

Coming from east of the west and west of the east, I thrive in international environments and gained experiences in Amsterdam, Ljubljana, Hamburg, Groningen, Brussels, and Amman. I believe that the future belongs to those who question which led me to establish Taking Up Space - Institute for Fair Shared Places where we do research and advocate for gender equality in analogue and digital spaces. 

Subscribe to my newsletter at tincalukan.substack.com

projects:
[{'title': 'Harvard metaLAB: From Telegrams to Telepathic Memos - The Future of Trust & Truth Online', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Communication is at the core of what it means to be human. And today, most of that communication is technologically mediated. As our communication systems change, the risks evolve alongside the benefits. We now see it daily: mis- and disinformation campaigns, polarization, surveillance, the undermining of social infrastructures. 

We developed answers for the questions:
How do the design and incentives of social media companies influence individual choices and major social movements?
Where are we headed? 
What do we want to create—and what do we want to leave behind? 
How can we work toward building the forms of connection that we (or others) would like to see, while also mitigating the risks?', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Tinca', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'PhD Candidate in Creator Economy & Culture | #SciComm TikTok Creator'}]}, {'title': 'The Hustle Economy', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Today, all entrepreneurship is digital. But, while Silicon Valley startups may celebrate their ability to platform small-scale businesses, the turn to digital economies is a response to precarious employment. It is a hustle that shows how risk has devolved from states and employers to workers. Though hustling often refers to outside-work activities and informal economies, it has always been and continues to be a mainstay of producing economic security for households across the world. It is also recognized as a property of racial capitalism, as a cultural form that adheres to some bodies but not others, as the hustle is associated with Black women in the United States, for instance, and with similarly gendered, raced, classed and casted bodies throughout the world.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Tinca', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'PhD Candidate in Creator Economy & Culture | #SciComm TikTok Creator'}]}, {'title': 'Societal Challenge Lab', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': 'Participated in an extra-curriculum project Societal Challenge Lab, tasks included applying scientific knowledge to the societal challenge of migration. In the group of twelve students, we developed policy and intervention to improve integration of the first generation migrants to the labour market in the Netherlands. I worked under time pressure and interviewed many experts and refugees.
', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Tinca', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'PhD Candidate in Creator Economy & Culture | #SciComm TikTok Creator'}]}, {'title': 'The Social Life of Algorithmic Harms', 'date': {'start': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': None, 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Tinca', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'PhD Candidate in Creator Economy & Culture | #SciComm TikTok Creator'}]}]
